==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[coler]], [[acoler]] ‘accoll, throw arms round neck of’, ultimately Latin [[ad]] + [[collum]] ‘neck’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /kɒl/

===Verb===
'''coll'''
# to [[hug]] or [[embrace]]
#:*'''1995''': They kissed and '''colled''' in parks and fields and, better, a / Warm bed, her own. — Anthony Burgess, ''Byrne''